Doc,<br><br>
Don't you know that the Marine Corp is one of the few places where the clothes don't make the man.  Where do you think they coined the word naked agression.  The corp.  No clothes required.  Right COOK.<br><br>
Doc, let you in on a secret.  High school and college.  Long hair.  I mean no haircut for four years and big mustache.  Sandles or loafers with no socks, ever.  Long before it became popular.  I was called all those names you were called.<br><br>
Did it mostly for the chicks, but mainly because it PISSED the establishment off.  Worked until they threatened to kick me out of school for non-conformity.  They didn't know the real me.<br><br>
When I stepped off the bus at boot camp they had a field day with me.   Stayed on the ragged edge.  Very irreverant.  I was asked to grow up or not go to flight school.  The rest is history.<br><br>
You see all hippies didn't hate the war.  Some like me liked it so much they never left.<br><br>
Thought you might enjoy this.  (REAL STORY)
